719506f-a.text:
East Houston Street, (entire left and the foreground of the right) west from (No. 270) but not including Ave. B. The triangular structure (No. 2-4 Ave A ) divides this street from East 1st Street, which the portion on the right becomes, when west of Ave. A. Note the 1st Street Station of the Second Ave. Elevated Line, on First Ave.

March 13, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

716418f-a.text:
Avenue B, west side, north from Houston Street.

April 3, 1935.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer
716418f-a.folder: Avenue B & Houston Street, Manhattan, NY

719505f-a.text:
East Houston Street, north side, west from (No. 270), but not including Ave. B. This side of East Houston Street, becomes East 1st Street, when west of Ave. A. Note the Station of the Second and Third Aves., Elevated on First Ave.

April 3, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
